***(ID)                            JES2B313
***(SUBSYSTEM)                     JES2
***(DESIGNER)                      D.H.CARTWRIGHT
***(AUTHOR)                        D.H.CARTWRIGHT
*
***(DATE WRITTEN)                  MARCH 1977
***(DATE TESTED)                   MARCH 1977
***(DATE INSTALLED)                MARCH 1977
*
***(ABSTRACT)
*
*        TO ENABLE THE OPERATORS TO MORE EASILY IDENTIFY PUNCHED OUTPUT,
*         ADD THE JOB'S NAME AND NUMBER TO THE HEADER CARD.
*
***(LOGIC SUMMARY)
*
*        AT APPROPRIATE POINT IN THE PUNCH SEPARATOR LACE CARD ROUTINE
*         IN HASPPRPU MODULE, EXIT WITH AN UNQUALIFIED $CBAL, THUS :-
*
*               $CBAL JES2B313                              Q1687200
*
*        IN THE EXIT ITSELF, PREPARE AN AREA TO RECEIVE THE JOB NAME,
*         BY REDUCING THE LENGTH OF THE 3RD AND 4TH CHARACTER OF ROOM
*         NUMBER FROM 8 TO 4 AND MOVE THE JOB NAME FROM JCT INTO
*         8 POSITIONS RECOVERED.
*
*
***(INSTALLATION)
*
*        THIS MOD. IS DYNAMICALLY LOADED AT INITILISATION TIME
*         UPON REQUEST VIA AN 'EXIT=' CONTROL CARD.
*
***(TESTING)
*
*        TO TEST :-
*
*         SUBMIT AND EXECUTE THE JOB 'TESTB313' WITH THE JES2 TEST SYSTEM.
*
*         YOU WILL FIND THIS JOB IN 'LIBRARYN.MVS' DATA SET,
*           MEMBER 'TESTB313', PASSWORD 'T313'.
*
*
*        RESULT TO BE OBTAINED :-
*
*        CHECK IF THE NAME OF THIS JOB IS PUNCHED IN THE MIDDLE
*         OF THE LACE CARD.
